snippet.textDisplay:
Okay, so, regarding the first dilemma, I would keep it up for as long as I could, but if it came down to it, I'd forget next morning and probably lose the job. Which is okay, because I'm not that worried about it. Some other job will hire, because even if they say negative things about me, like "can't follow instruction", there will always be a demand for workers. Simple jobs, like truck unloaders, shelf stockers, maintenance, etc. are simple jobs that they will literally take anyone for.


In regards to the birthday celebrations, it doesn't matter to me what we do for my birthday, as long as it's nice and I'm in good company. :)


For policies like that one, it usually is because of a quality thing, or safety. I think I've only encountered one place though that did this? I can't even remember where or why. Meh.


Jomm, let me tell you, your mom is rude af. xD You should've dragged her over to the bathroom table. Besides, that's easy bathroom access, so you don't have to walk/run/waddle so far. I def wouldn't have minded the bathroom table.
